{
  "stem": "11723.5",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "If the Bosnians-- if any Bosnian could get away from the site of fighting, they could live in peace.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We had no place to go because all of Europe was-- almost all of Europe was occupied by the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "America didn't want us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "England didn't want us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Nobody wanted us.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We had no way out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And also, somehow history is a tableau of persecutions and all sorts of tragedies, like during the uh, Middle Ages there were pogroms.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And even before that, there were the Crusades.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And in the name of Jesus, lots and lots of people were killed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The pogroms were localized.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So one village was totally wiped out maybe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But other villages remained.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "There was a way to get away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Somehow, the conqueror always massacred the vanquished.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But this wasn't the same way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "This was not the same way, because you couldn't get away from it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Becoming a Christian didn't help, because if the blood was not Aryan, if  it was not pure, even if your grandparents were Jewish, you were a Jew.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "The Nazis-- changing religion didn't mean anything, because the Nazis were racist.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And they considered the Jews a race.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "It wasn't considered a religion.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "So changing your-- becoming a Catholic or Protestant didn't change anything, really.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And you couldn't get away from it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And to my descendants, I want to leave a message.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Against incredible odds, I have survived this horrible Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And I find it that it is my duty to continue the traditions of Judaism.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And the only way I can do that is to have my children remain Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And that's why I'm so adamant about my children marrying Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
